Text.Value: The Wulbren I know - the one who skipped rocks with me in the Underdark... he's still in there. I know it.
Gondians respond well to reason. So when you meet them - be reasonable.

EditorData.logicalname: Agreed to speak to the Gondians

Text.Value: If you don't shut up, I'll detonate the bomb right now.
Something is wrong. Very wrong.
You have. But the lives of many people are at a stake. You are a hero, aren't you? Isn't saving people what heroes do?
I think Wulbren would like to know you're undermining him.
You did well refusing Wulbren's proposition but I fear he'll find some fool who'll plant his bomb.
If only Wulbren shared your sentiments.
The Gondians deserve a chance to plead their case before being blown to pieces. Please, find out what's going on?
They have to die, Barcus.
You would turn your back on innocent people? That's... not like you.
You look worried.
A fanatic with no thought for innocent life.
'Not now' yourself! The Gondians... it can't be as it seems.
Any luck?
All right - I'll speak to them.
The Gondians are inventors - just like us. Similarly persnickety and self-important, too.
There you are. Good. We need to strategise.

EditorData.NodeContext: Clearly a little surprised to see the player again

Text.Value: Please. Speak to them before you do anything. They deserve a chance to plead their case before being blown to pieces, don't you think?
Questions first. Violence later. And only if absolutely necessary.
Be firm with Wulbren. But not too firm. Let him have his say, but don't let him talk over you. Got it? Good.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little distracted; he's lost in his thoughts

Text.Value: It's a radical plan. I want nothing to do with it.
That's all I ask.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wryly. You don't owe him anything. The opposite, maybe.

Text.Value: Leave.
You don't know me as well as you thought.
Haven't I done enough for you?
I have no secrets from Wulbren. And anyway, my very presence is a thorn in his side.
I want nothing to do with any of this - you're on your own.
I think there's more to this than meets the eye.
I can't save everyone.
I am. I knew him rash, but this is... unspeakable. Speak to him - help him see sense. Someone has to.
You're right - I'll try to contact the Gondians.
The Gondians must be stopped - they're working for the Absolute.
They are inventors - just like us. Persnickety and self-important, too, but we all have our moments.
So it appears.
I cannot believe that - and I don't think you believe it either.
Wulbren is planning something. Lots of moving parts. I'm still trying to suss the details myself.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little distracted; he has a lot on his mind

Text.Value: Some. But what he has planned is... unthinkable. Maybe you can help him see sense. Someone has to.
I'd rather continue to prick his conscience than to be silently complicit in an atrocity.
Not now, Barcus.
The Gondians are people, no different to you or I. Don't harm them.
True. But I thought you might at least try.
A runepowder bomb... What the devil has he become?
All right. I'll try to contact them.
But his hate for the Gondians has blinded him. He believes they work for the Absolute willingly, but it's not true. I'm sure of it.
You'll hear no argument on that score. But using runepowder on the Gondians?!

Synopsis: Barcus dialog in gnomes hideout cellar in WYR Rivington (he's in act1 and act2). Gives player a quest to investigate Gondian workshop.
